<h3>Unstyled List</h3>
<ul class="list-unstyled">
  <li>Basically a list</li>
  <li>With no bullets</li>
  <li>Lorem ipsum</li>
</ul>


<h3>Inline List</h3>
<p><strong>The following demonstrates usage of flex classes, gap classes (see spacer utilities for more information) and breakpoint-specific classes.</strong></p>
<ul class="list-unstyled flex g-4">
  <li>Basically a list</li>
  <li>That displays items<br /> side by side</li>
  <li>Lorem ipsum</li>
</ul>

<ul class="list-unstyled flex g-4 items-center">
  <li>Same inline list</li>
  <li>But vertically aligned<br /> to middle</li>
  <li>Lorem ipsum</li>
</ul>

<ul class="list-unstyled flex flex-col lg:flex-row g-4">
  <li>Same inline list</li>
  <li>But stacks on mobile</li>
  <li>Lorem ipsum</li>
</ul>


<ul class="list-unstyled flex g-3">
  <li>Same inline list</li>
  <li>But closer together</li>
  <li>Lorem ipsum</li>
</ul>

<ul class="list-unstyled flex g-6">
  <li>Same inline list</li>
  <li>But further apart</li>
  <li>Lorem ipsum</li>
</ul>

<h3>Divided List</h3>
<p>Uses border classes so you can control the border color.</p>
<ul class="list-unstyled  flex lh-1">
  {% for i in 1..3 %}
    <li class="{{ loop.last == false ? 'border-right-1 border-gray mr-1 pr-1' : '' }}">Inline list</li>
  {% endfor %}
</ul>
